  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why is Quora eliminating topic-based moderation?",
  "response": "Quora's decision to eliminate topic-based moderators was part of a broader strategy to refine their moderation system. The move was announced in late 2021 and implemented in early 2022. The primary reasons for this change include:\n\n1. **Unified Moderation System**: Quora aimed to streamline its moderation process by moving towards a more centralized system. Instead of having topic-specific moderators, they wanted a more cohesive approach that could ensure consistent enforcement of policies across all topics.\n\n2. **Scalability and Efficiency**: Managing a large number of topic-based moderators can be complex and resource-intensive. By shifting to a centralized team of moderators, Quora hoped to improve efficiency and scalability, enabling them to handle the growing volume of content more effectively.\n\n3. **Quality and Consistency**: Quora believed that a centralized moderation team would lead to more consistent decision-making and higher overall content quality. With a unified team, they could better train moderators and maintain uniform standards across the platform.\n\n4. **Focus on Core Features**: By simplifying the moderation structure, Quora could redirect resources towards improving other aspects of the platform, such as enhancing user experience, developing new features, and strengthening algorithms for content recommendation.\n\nWhile some users expressed concerns about the potential loss of specialized knowledge and nuanced understanding that topic-based moderators provided, Quora assured that they would continue to value and incorporate expert input in other ways, such as through their existing network of topic followers and contributors.",
